<TITLE> Israel says car bomb defused at shopping mall </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JERUSALEM, Sun Mar 22,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Prime Minister Ehud Olmert said on Sunday an explosives-laden car parked outside a shopping mall in northern Israel, and defused by police, was an attempted Arab attack aimed at causing mass casualties. "A huge disaster was prevented last night in Haifa after a car packed with dozens of kilos of explosives did not explode," Olmert said at the weekly cabinet meeting. Israeli media reported a little-known armed faction called Liberators of the Galilee had claimed responsibility for planting the bomb in the mall's parking lot in the port city of Haifa on Saturday. The name of the group -- the Galilee is inside Israel -- suggested that it was comprised of Israeli Arabs. Olmert did not use the word "Palestinians" in his comments on the car bomb, but said the West Bank had long been a "stepping off point" for attacks inside Israel. "A preliminary investigation shows it was a terrorist infrastructure operating with great sophistication and aiming to carry out a mass-casualty attack," he said, without naming any group. The Liberators of the Galilee were quoted as saying they wanted to avenge Israel's demolition of Palestinian homes in Jerusalem and the recent Israeli military offensive in Gaza. A small blast, possibly caused by a botched detonation, drew the attention of police to the parking lot, said police spokesman Mickey Rosenfeld. They found a "large explosive" in the car and called in bomb disposal experts, said Rosen
